gui_save_flightline(25.10)                          gui_save_flightline(25.10)

Name
       gui_save_flightline  - Saves the flightline information of the selected
       instance to the specified file

Syntax
       gui_save_flightline

       [-help]

       -file <file_name>

       [-netWindow]

       Saves the flightline information of the selected instance to the speci-
       fied file.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description of the gui_save_flightline command.

              For a detailed description of the command, use the man  command:
              man gui_save_flightline.

       -file <file_name>
              Specifies  the name of the file in which the flightline informa-
              tion will be saved.

       -netWindow
              Saves the contents of the Flightline Net Window.

Example
       The following command saves the flightline information to a file  named
       flight1:

       gui_save_flightline -file flight1

